President Donald J. Trump announced his intention to nominate several individuals for key positions in his administration. 

- Irwin Steven Goldstein of New York is nominated to be the Under Secretary for Public Diplomacy at the Department of State. He has extensive experience in communications and has worked in both the private and public sectors.

- Joseph H. Hunt of Maryland is nominated to be an Assistant Attorney General, Civil Division. He currently serves as Chief of Staff and Senior Counselor to the Attorney General and has supervised the Government's litigation efforts in Federal district courts.

- Robert Hunter Kurtz of Virginia is nominated to be an Assistant Secretary of Housing and Urban Development, Public and Indian Housing. He currently serves as the Deputy Chief of Staff for Policy and Programs at HUD and has experience in housing policy at both the local and Federal levels.

- Sean P. Lawler of Maryland is nominated to be Chief of Protocol and to have the rank of Ambassador. He currently serves as the Director for Visits, Planning, and Diplomatic Affairs at the National Security Council and has previous military experience.

Additionally, President Trump announced his intention to appoint Richard V. Burkhauser of Texas as a Member of the Council of Economic Advisors. Burkhauser has focused on how public policies affect vulnerable populations and is currently an adjunct professor at the University of Texas at Austin.

These nominations and appointments are subject to Senate confirmation.